column43: Q4 (Which option do you support?) I support Option 1 to remove the Liveable Streets closures and make public realm improvements to the wider area.
column44: Q4 (Which option do you support?) I support Option 2 to retain the existing traffic arrangements
column45: Q5 (To what extent do you agree or disagree with the proposed changes set out in option 1:) Removal of closures on Canrobert Street, Punderson’s Gardens, Teesdale Street, Clarkson Street and Old Bethnal Green Road.
column46: Q5 (To what extent do you agree or disagree with the proposed changes set out in option 1:) Retention of the closures on Pollard Row and Pollard Street and creation of a new public realm in the area with new seating, planting and trees.  This is the retention of a closure to northbound traffic on Pollard Row (at the junction of Ivimey Street) and a closure to traffic travelling eastbound on Pollard Street (at the junction with Pollard Row). The plans on page 6 of the consultation document also propose the removal of closures that currently restrict westbound traffic on Pollard Street and southbound traffic on Pollard Row.

column20: Long Covid like syndrome following Moderna vaccine

Please note that putting Autism in a category with head injury and learning disability is somewhat offensive and inaccurate. I would describe it as a cognitive difference not an impairment. Using the social model of disability this feels more accurate.
